# When to Use Production Practices - Decision Framework

## Quick Decision Tree

Ask yourself these 3 questions:

### 1. Who will use this?
```
Just me
  → Use BASIC practices
  → Example: Personal learning project

Classmates (10-50 users)
  → Use MEDIUM practices
  → Example: Class directory, group project

Real business (100+ users)
  → Use FULL practices
  → Example: Aling Rosa's sari-sari store POS

Government/Critical
  → Use CRITICAL practices (all + extras)
  → Example: Barangay certificate system
```

### 2. What happens if it breaks?
```
I get a bad grade
  → Use BASIC practices
  
Users annoyed but not critical
  → Use MEDIUM practices
  
Business loses money
  → Use FULL practices
  
Legal/safety problems
  → Use CRITICAL practices
```

### 3. How long will it run?
```
1 week demo
  → Use BASIC practices
  
1 semester (3-4 months)
  → Use MEDIUM practices
  
6+ months
  → Use FULL practices
  
Permanent/indefinite
  → Use CRITICAL practices
```

## Practice Levels Explained

### BASIC (School Projects)

**Use These:**
- ✅ Try-catch for database operations
- ✅ Basic error page (custom 404 and 500)
- ✅ .gitignore (node_modules, .env)
- ✅ README with setup instructions

**Skip These:**
- ❌ Winston logging (console.log is fine)
- ❌ Automatic backups (no cron needed)
- ❌ External monitoring (Railway metrics enough)
- ❌ Advanced security (no Helmet, CSRF, rate limiting)
- ❌ Performance optimization (not critical yet)

**Why:**
- Focus on learning core concepts
- Don't overwhelm with complexity
- 1-2 weeks only
- Teacher is only user

**Example Projects:**
- Barangay directory for class demo
- Sari-sari store inventory (learning exercise)
- Grade 9-Einstein attendance tracker

**Time to Implement:** 30 minutes

---

### MEDIUM (Personal/Group Projects)

**Use These:**
- ✅ Try-catch + error middleware
- ✅ Winston logging (info level)
- ✅ .env for any secrets (session secret, API keys)
- ✅ Manual backups (download button in admin)
- ✅ Basic health check (/health endpoint)
- ✅ Helmet (one line of code - why not?)

**Skip These:**
- ❌ Automatic backups (manual weekly is fine)
- ❌ UptimeRobot (Railway metrics enough for low stakes)
- ❌ CSRF protection (if no forms or read-only)
- ❌ Rate limiting (low traffic)
- ❌ Advanced performance (not needed yet)

**Why:**
- Balance learning with reasonable practices
- Used by classmates, not strangers
- Runs for 1 semester
- Not critical if it goes down for an hour

**Example Projects:**
- Class section directory (40 classmates use it)
- Personal portfolio with contact form
- Group project: Barangay website

**Time to Implement:** 2-3 hours

---

### FULL (Real Business/Client Projects)

**Use These:**
- ✅ ALL security practices:
  - Helmet
  - CSRF protection
  - Rate limiting
  - Input validation
  - Parameterized queries
- ✅ Winston logging (debug in dev, info in prod)
- ✅ Automatic daily backups (cron)
- ✅ UptimeRobot monitoring
- ✅ Performance optimization:
  - Compression
  - Caching
  - Query optimization
  - Pagination
- ✅ Complete error handling
- ✅ Health checks with database validation

**Skip These:**
- Nothing! Use everything in the lecture.

**Why:**
- Real money at stake
- Real users depend on it
- Owner expects reliability
- Runs 24/7
- Downtime costs sales

**Example Projects:**
- Aling Rosa's sari-sari store POS system
- Barangay San Juan resident directory
- Small business inventory management

**Time to Implement:** 8-12 hours (spread over days)

---

### CRITICAL (Government/High-Stakes Systems)

**Use These:**
- ✅ EVERYTHING from FULL level
- ✅ PLUS: Audit logging (who did what, when, from where)
- ✅ PLUS: Offsite backups (email weekly, Google Drive monthly)
- ✅ PLUS: Multiple alert contacts (email + SMS + Slack)
- ✅ PLUS: Formal testing (written test cases, UAT with users)
- ✅ PLUS: Documentation (user manual, admin guide, troubleshooting)
- ✅ PLUS: Compliance (data privacy, security policies)

**Why:**
- Public service responsibility
- Legal requirements (data privacy, audit trails)
- High reliability requirements
- Many concurrent users
- Data cannot be lost
- Security breaches have serious consequences

**Example Projects:**
- Barangay certificate issuance system
- Government permit application portal
- School enrollment system with grades

**Time to Implement:** 20-40 hours (proper project)

