## Red Flags (Common Mistakes)

### ❌ Mistake 1: Using EVERYTHING for a 1-week demo
**Problem:**
- Wastes time on setup instead of learning
- Over-complicates simple project
- Misses the point of the assignment

**Fix:**
- Use only BASIC practices
- Focus on features, not production
- Save advanced practices for real projects

---

### ❌ Mistake 2: Using NOTHING for a real business
**Problem:**
- Data loss risk
- Security vulnerabilities
- Angry customers
- Lost money
- Reputation damage

**Fix:**
- Use FULL practices
- 8-12 hours setup is worth it
- Client deserves reliability

---

### ❌ Mistake 3: Copying practices without understanding
**Problem:**
- "My friend uses Winston, so I will too"
- Don't know why or when to use it
- Can't explain to teacher/client

**Fix:**
- Understand WHY each practice exists
- Use decision framework above
- Choose appropriate level for YOUR project

---

### ❌ Mistake 4: Premature optimization
**Problem:**
- Optimizing before performance problems exist
- "My site loads in 0.5 seconds but I'll add caching anyway"
- Wastes time on non-issues

**Fix:**
- Make it work first
- Optimize if slow (> 3 seconds)
- Test on 3G connection first
- Use Lighthouse to find real bottlenecks

---

## The Golden Rule

> **Start simple. Add practices as needed.**
>
> Begin with BASIC practices. As your project grows in importance, users, or duration, add more practices.
>
> Don't overwhelm yourself trying to use everything at once.

